An estimated 20 passengers, all believed to be educators travelling to Polokwane from Senwabarwana, were rushed to hospital with injuries after the vehicle they were traveling in reportedly overturned on the Mogwadi road between the city and Makgodu this evening.
According to persons on the scene the accident happened around 17:30 after the vehicle got a puncture and overturned.
While Polokwane Observer was at the scene no law enforcers had arrived as yet. By then several ambulances from both the Department of Health and private institutions were spotted en route to the city reportedly rushing patients to Pietersburg Provincial Hospital.
Story: Endy Senyatsi